<br>
I am writing this post in order to apologize to the Everquest community.  I am not apologizing for my actions, but more so for any inconvenience they may have caused to any honest Everquest players.<br>
<br>
As you all may have heard, a certain 'banker' bug was advertised recently.  I made that scenario up completely; there was no truth in it whatsoever.  However, before anyone jumps to conclusions I would at least like to explain in some detail what my plan was, and what I did to help the game.<br>
<br>
Like I said, the banker issue was false.  I also knew about 3 other 'real' exploits with platinum.  My plan was to submit the true bugs to the devs to be fixed, but I knew that their response time is usually not very good, and even if it was, I wanted this fixed asap.  I play this game 40 hours a week, and I would hate to see it ruined by cheaters.  In order to make them work faster, I fabricated a fairly believable scheme to make public.  I posted the banker information on two boards, and it made it to every major server board and even the live &quot;Newbie Zone&quot; forum.  Absor himself was posting anti-dupe threads within 10 hours of the initial post I made.  Within a day there was a patch with a message theme of &quot;cracking down on exploiters&quot;.  That banker sure made it big and fast, even beyond my expectations.<br>
<br>
I believe my plan actually resulted in a positive action being taken.  If for any reason my false advertising caused you to waste time looking in Befallen, or any other detriment to your play experience, I apologize formally.  I also apologize to the Developers or whoever investigated the platinum issue.  I believe the banker was extremely easy for them to prove fake, but if it wasted any of their time at all, I am at fault.  This was the best plan I could come up with to aid the fixation of this issue, hopefully the means justifies the ends <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
